content._richtextfield:Lyrics: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 1" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="May you run and " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="not be weary" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="May your heart " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="be filled with song." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And may the " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="love of God continue" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="To give you hope " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="and keep you strong." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 2" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And may you run" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="and not be weary" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="May your life " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="be filled with joy!" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And may the road " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="you travel always" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text=" lead you home." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And may the road " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="you travel always " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="lead you home." /></Paragraph>

content._richtextfield:Lyrics: <Paragraph><Run Text="Verse 1" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="Here in this place" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="new light is streaming," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="now is the darkness" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="vanished away;" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="see in this space" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="our fears and our dreamings" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="brought here to you" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="in the light of this day." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="Gather us in," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="the lost and forsaken," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="gather us in," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="the blind and the lame;" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="call to us now," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="and we shall awaken," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="we shall arise" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="at the sound of our name." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="Verse 2" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="We are the young," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="our lives are a mystery," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="we are the old" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="who yearn for your face;" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="we have been sung" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="throughout all of history," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="called to be light" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="to the whole human race." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="Gather us in," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="the rich and the haughty," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="gather us in," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="the proud and the strong;" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="give us a heart," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="so meek and so lowly," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="give us the courage" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="to enter the song." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="Verse 3" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="Here we will take" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="the wine and the water," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="here we will take" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="the bread of new birth," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="here you shall call" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="your sons and your daughters," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="call us anew" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="to be salt for the earth." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="Give us to drink" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="the wine of compassion," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="give us to eat" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="the bread that is you;" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="nourish us well," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="and teach us to fashion" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="lives that are holy" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="and hearts that are true." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="Verse 4" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="Not in the dark" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="of buildings confining," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="not in some heaven," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="light years away\u2014" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="but here in this place" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="the new light is shining," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="now is the kingdom," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="now is the day." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="Gather us in" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="and hold us forever," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="gather us in" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="and make us your own;" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="gather us in," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="all peoples together," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="fire of love" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="in our flesh and our bone." /></Paragraph>

content._richtextfield:Lyrics: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Chorus 1" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="So welcome" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="welcome each other" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The old and the youthful" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The fit and the faint" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Welcome sister and brother" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Welcome the seeker" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The sinner the saint" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 1" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The house of our God" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Is not just for the holy" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The house of our God" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Is not just for the wise" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Come in and be one" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="With the common and" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="the lowly" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Who wait with the hunger" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="For God in their eyes" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 2" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The table of God is not" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Just for the certain" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The bread and the cup" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Are not just for the pure" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The cross of the Christ" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Has torn back the curtain" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The temple thrown open" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="For the searching and sure" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 3" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The household of God" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Is not just for the wealthy" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The safe and the settled" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The well placed and known" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The people of God know" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The struggle is healthy" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And conflict is better" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Than calm all alone" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 4" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The work of our God" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Is not just for the clever" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The service of God" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Is not just for the strong" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The way of the cross" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Is a journey forever" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="So gather to pray" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Then we'll travel along" /></Paragraph>

content._richtextfield:Passage: <Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0" TextIndent="18"><Run Text="When he noticed how the guests chose the places of honor, he told them a parable. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0" TextIndent="18"><Run Text="âWhen you are invited by someone to a wedding banquet, do not sit down at the place of honor, in case someone more distinguished than you has been invited by your host; " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0" TextIndent="18"><Run Text="and the host who invited both of you may come and say to you, âGive this person your place,â and then in disgrace you would start to take the lowest place. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0" TextIndent="18"><Run Text="But when you are invited, go and sit down at the lowest place, so that when your host comes, he may say to you, âFriend, move up higherâ; then you will be honored in the presence of all who sit at the table with you. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0" TextIndent="18"><Run Text="For all who exalt themselves will be humbled, and those who humble themselves will be exalted.â " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph /><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0" TextIndent="18"><Run Text="He said also to the one who had invited him, âWhen you give a luncheon or a dinner, do not invite your friends or your brothers or your relatives or rich neighbors, in case they may invite you in return, and you would be repaid. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0" TextIndent="18"><Run Text="But when you give a banquet, invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, and the blind. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0" TextIndent="18"><Run Text="And you will be blessed, because they cannot repay you, for you will be repaid at the resurrection of the righteous.â" /></Paragraph><Paragraph />

content._richtextfield:Passage: <Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,0" TextIndent="-36"><Run Text="Has a nation changed its gods, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,0" TextIndent="-9"><Run Text="even though they are no gods? " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,0" TextIndent="-18"><Run Text="But my people have changed their glory " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,0" TextIndent="-9"><Run Text="for something that does not profit. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" /><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,0" TextIndent="-36"><Run Text="Be appalled, O heavens, at this, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="16,0,0,0" TextIndent="-9"><Run Text="be shocked, be utterly desolate, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="20,0,0,0" TextIndent="-9"><Run Text="says the " /><Run FontCapitals="SmallCaps" Text="Lord" /><Run Text=", " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" /><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" /><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,0" TextIndent="-36"><Run Text="for my people have committed two evils: " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,0" TextIndent="-9"><Run Text="they have forsaken me, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,0" TextIndent="-18"><Run Text="the fountain of living water, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,0" TextIndent="-9"><Run Text="and dug out cisterns for themselves, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,0" TextIndent="-18"><Run Text="cracked cisterns " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="36,0,0,9" TextIndent="-9"><Run Text="that can hold no water." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" />

content._richtextfield:Lyrics: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 1" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We are your people:" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Spirit of grace," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="You dare to make us" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Christ to our neighbors" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Of every culture" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="and place." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 6" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Spirit, unite us," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="make us, by grace," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Willing and ready," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Christ's living body," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Loving the" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="whole human race." /></Paragraph>

content._richtextfield:Lyrics: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 1" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="As we gather" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="at your table," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="as we listen" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="to your word," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="help us know," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="O God, your presence;" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="let our hearts and" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="minds be stirred." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Nourish us with" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="sacred story" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="till we claim it" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="as our own;" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="teach us through" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="this holy banquet" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="how to make" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Love's victory known." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 2" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Turn our worship" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="into witness" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="in the sacrament" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="of life;" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="send us forth" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="to love and serve you," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="bringing peace" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="where there is strife." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Give us, Christ," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="your great compassion" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="to forgive" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="as you forgave;" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="may we still" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="behold your image" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="in the world" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="you died to save." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 3" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Gracious Spirit," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="help us summon" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="other guests to" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="share that feast" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="where triumphant" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Love will welcome" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="those who had been" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="last and least." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="There no more will" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="envy blind us" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="nor will pride" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="our peace destroy," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="as we join with" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="saints and angels" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="to repeat the" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="sounding joy." /></Paragraph>
